  ],
  "symbols": [
    {"repo": "github.com/sg-evals/etcd-io-etcd", "path": "raft/storage.go", "symbol": "ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable"},
    {"repo": "github.com/sg-evals/etcd-io-etcd", "path": "raft/log.go", "symbol": "snapshot"},
    {"repo": "github.com/sg-evals/etcd-io-etcd", "path": "raft/raft.go", "symbol": "maybeSendAppend"}
  ],
  "chain": [
    {"repo": "github.com/sg-evals/etcd-io-etcd", "path": "raft/raft.go", "symbol": "maybeSendAppend"},
    {"repo": "github.com/sg-evals/etcd-io-etcd", "path": "raft/log.go", "symbol": "snapshot"},
    {"repo": "github.com/sg-evals/etcd-io-etcd", "path": "raft/storage.go", "symbol": "ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable"}
  ],
  "text": "The ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable error is defined in raft/storage.go (lines 36-38) as a sentinel error returned by the Storage interface when a snapshot is temporarily unavailable. This error is used in the context of Raft log catch-up when a follower node needs to restore from a snapshot.\n\nThe error's primary usage occurs during the snapshot availability check in the Raft log catch-up process. When a leader node (in raft/raft.go) calls the maybeSendAppend() function (lines 432-489), it attempts to replicate log entries to a follower. If the follower's next required log index is too far behind (has been compacted and incorporated into a snapshot), the leader cannot send individual log entries. Instead, it must send a snapshot.\n\nThe flow works as follows:\n\n1. In maybeSendAppend() (raft/raft.go:432-489), the leader attempts to get the required term and entries from the raftLog (lines 440-441).\n\n2. If either the term or entries retrieval fails (line 446: errt != nil || erre != nil), this indicates the requested log index has been compacted. The leader then needs to send a snapshot instead.\n\n3. To obtain the snapshot, the leader calls r.raftLog.snapshot() (line 453), which is defined in raft/log.go (lines 204-209).\n\n4. The raftLog.snapshot() function first checks if there's a pending unstable snapshot. If not, it delegates to the storage layer by calling l.storage.Snapshot() (line 208).\n\n5. If the storage layer returns ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable (checked in raft/raft.go:455), this means the snapshot is not yet ready to be sent. The leader logs a debug message and returns false without sending the snapshot (lines 455-457), allowing the node to retry later.\n\nThis mechanism prevents a rejoin scenario where a node falls too far behind and requires snapshot-based recovery, but the snapshot is not yet available (perhaps still being prepared by the storage layer). The error signals that the Storage implementation needs more time to prepare the snapshot, and the Raft state machine should retry the operation later."
}

